# Protect curriculum database (grade 1–5 + Miscellaneous Words)

These six lessons are **frozen by default** — no writes without explicit user approval:

- **`grade 1`** (300 cards)
- **`grade 2`** (600 cards)
- **`grade 3`** (800 cards)
- **`grade 4`** (1000 cards)
- **`grade 5`** (1500 cards)
- **`Miscellaneous Words`** (195 cards)

## Never without explicit user approval

Do **not** read/write PGlite data for any of the six when it would:

- Reseed or sync cards
- Apply or bulk-restore images
- Change example sentences or translations
- Rebuild Miscellaneous Words (`create-miscellaneous-words-lesson.mjs`)
- Run `pnpm db:restore-all` steps for these lessons without skip/confirm

**Do not** run `db:reset` if it would destroy these lessons without explicit user approval.

**Always stop `pnpm dev`** before maintenance scripts (`scripts/lib/db-safety.mjs`).

## When the user asks to change any frozen lesson

Stop and show this warning **in Arabic**, then wait for **نعم** or **لا**:

> ⚠️ **تحذير:** طلبك يعدّل قاعدة بيانات أحد دروس المنهج المحمية (**grade 1 / grade 2 / grade 3 / grade 4 / grade 5 / Miscellaneous Words**).
> **هل تريد المتابعة؟** (نعم / لا)

- **لا** → do not touch their DB.
- **نعم** → `GRADE123_DB_WRITE_CONFIRMED=1` or `CURRICULUM_DB_WRITE_CONFIRMED=1` then run scripts.

## Safe without confirmation

- Read-only: `audit-curriculum-lessons.mjs`, `show-misc-card.mjs`, `show-grade*-card.mjs`, `snapshot-curriculum-lessons.mjs`, `audit-grade5-images.mjs`
- Daniel and Miscellaneous Words Part 1 (hidden source lessons)
- Adding **new** lessons/images that do not touch the six frozen lessons

## After user says نعم

```powershell
$env:GRADE123_DB_WRITE_CONFIRMED="1"; node scripts/apply-grade5-word.mjs hypotenuse
```

Remove the env var after the operation.

## Verify integrity (read-only)

```powershell
node scripts/audit-curriculum-lessons.mjs
node scripts/snapshot-curriculum-lessons.mjs
```

Snapshot is saved to `.data/curriculum-snapshot.json`.
